                    <div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-1"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig1" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 1: In situ and operando probing of electrochemical organic oxidation reactions (OORs).</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41570-025-00767-7/MediaObjects/41570_2025_767_Fig1_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-1-1" src="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41570-025-00767-7/MediaObjects/41570_2025_767_Fig1_HTML.png" alt="" loading="lazy" width="279" height="312"></picture><span class="u-visually-hidden" id="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-1-1">The alternative text for this image may have been generated using AI.</span></div></div></figure></div><div class="c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="figure" data-container-section="figure" id="figure-2"><figure><figcaption><b id="Fig2" class="c-article-section__figure-caption" data-test="figure-caption-text">Fig. 2: In situ and operando techniques used to investigate organic oxidation reactions.</b></figcaption><div class="c-article-section__figure-content"><div class="c-article-section__figure-item"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41570-025-00767-7/MediaObjects/41570_2025_767_Fig2_HTML.png?as=webp"><img aria-describedby="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-2-1" src="//media.springernature.com/m312/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41570-025-00767-7/MediaObjects/41570_2025_767_Fig2_HTML.png" alt="" loading="lazy" width="312" height="269"></picture><span class="u-visually-hidden" id="ai-alt-disclaimer-figure-2